11/06/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and President Ion Iliescu agreed Tuesday (10 June) on the need to restructure the government and reduce the number of ministries. 
After their meeting, Iliescu said they had agreed the changes should be introduced by the end of this month. 
The number of ministries would likely be reduced from 23 to 17, in a bid to increase efficiency. 
(Nine o'Clock, Mediafax - 11/06/03)
